images.alt: Surreal dreamy scene illustration, with the main subject being a pink-themed subway car. The floor inside is covered with lush green grass, dotted with pink, white, and yellow wildflowers and small white floral patterns; the seats, handrails, and ceiling are all pink. Both sides and the top of the car are adorned with pink-purple, pink-white, and yellow flowers (such as daisies and baby's breath). The scene is set inside the subway, with the outside windows showing a blurred city street, creating the atmosphere of a 'natural secret garden in the city.' The style blends realistic scene construction with fairytale aesthetics, with pink and green as the primary colors, complemented by a variety of flower colors, delivering a sweet and charming element. The composition uses depth, extending from one end of the car to the other to enhance the sense of space. Details include the delicate texture of the grass, the layered colors and gradients of the flowers, the smooth texture of the pink seats, and the natural drooping of the flowers on the ceiling, presenting an overall healing, sweet surreal subway floral-themed illustration. Not meant to be depressing or sad.  The reality is that my time already spent on earth is much greater than my time left.  What will it be like?  Will there only be our minds and what we imagine in our mind. No physical being but still our thoughts and feelings.  If there is no need for food, shelter, or possessions then work is of no value.  But creativity for itself would blossom further in our minds.   Whether it is shared with others or just ourselves it will be endless. 

Is social media with creating art and no physical connection a glimpse at a different situation? 

Just some thoughts and Me at some time.

#Astro-Paranoia ’57: A 7-Day Retro-Cosmic Challenge

Style: Atomic-Age Pulp Sci-Fi
Influence: The Day the Earth Stood Still × Forbidden Planet × EC Comics Weird Science × Cold War cosmic dread × retrofuturist paperback covers.

Nov 18: The Transmission from Sector 9
A garbled distress call reaches Earth — containing a human voice no one sent.

Nov 19: The Astronaut Who Returned… Mostly
A spacefarer emerges from his capsule smiling, though half his shadow lags behind.

Nov 20: The Ray That Learned to Think
A lab experiment in atomic light gains awareness, bending itself toward the nearest heartbeat.

Nov 21: The City That Blinked
For one full second, every building disappears — replaced by a mirror of a future that fears us.

Nov 22: Visitors in the Vacuum Diner
Late-night travelers stop by a chrome-and-neon diner floating above the desert — none of them order food.

Nov 23: The Star That Followed Me Home
A tiny burning point of light drifts behind a child, humming in a familiar voice.

Nov 24: Planet X Has Already Landed
The astronomers announce discovery — but its influence has been here for decades.
